item.title: NSW reveals major quarantine change
item.description: The NSW government is expected to announce a home quarantine trial for international arrivals on Friday.

item.title: US moves to block Purdue Pharma opioid settlement
item.description: The US Justice Department has challenged a plan that would dissolve Purdue Pharma, manufacturer of the OxyContin drug that has been blamed for the country's opioid crisis, while shielding its founders from lawsuits.

item.title: Russians start voting in parliamentary polls after historic crackdown
item.description: Russians in the Far East began voting in a three-day parliamentary election in which vocal Kremlin critics have been barred from running following a historic crackdown on the opposition.

item.title: NSW records 1284 new virus cases
item.description: Another 1284 Covid cases and 12 deaths have been recorded in NSW, as the daily case numbers continue to show signs of stabilising.

item.title: IMF chief denies altering World Bank report to appease China
item.description: IMF chief Kristalina Georgieva on Thursday disputed an independent investigation which found that in her previous job at the World Bank, she pressed staff to alter a report to avoid angering China.

item.title: Intruder dead in bungled break-in
item.description: An intruder who tried to force his way into a home in Melbourne’s southeast is dead after he was allegedly stabbed in the chest during a scuffle.

item.title: Giant sequoias wrapped in foil to protect from US forest fires
item.description: The world's biggest trees were being wrapped in fire-proof blankets Thursday in an effort to protect them from huge blazes tearing through the drought-stricken western United States.

item.title: US reality show ‘The Activist’ backtracks after uproar
item.description: Creators of a new reality show pitting activists promoting charitable causes against each other were forced to change course following a massive backlash, with a top star apologizing Thursday for her participation.

item.title: Covid response ‘criminalised half the city’
item.description: Extra-tough lockdown rules and heavy policing in Sydney’s west and southwest have “criminalised” half the city, multicultural representatives have said.
